STEP 5b: COMPUTE EDGE THRESHOLD (data-driven)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  For each CUI, take its LAST (19th) neighbor's distance.
  That's the weakest connection.

  RA's 19th neighbor distance:     1 - 0.05 = 0.95
  Methotrexate's 19th distance:    1 - 0.03 = 0.97
  CRP's 19th distance:             1 - 0.04 = 0.96
  ...

  threshold = mean of all 19th-neighbor distances
            = mean([0.95, 0.97, 0.96, ...])
            ≈ 0.60

  This means: cosine distance < 0.60 → add edge.
  Equivalent: cosine similarity > 0.40 → add edge.


