STEP 6: HAC DEDUP WITHIN EACH TOPIC
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Topic 0 [Inflammatory Arthritis]:
    Pairwise distances within topic:
      RA ↔ RA of knee:     0.02  (near-identical)
      RA ↔ Arthritis:      0.05
      RA ↔ OA:             0.10
      Arthritis ↔ OA:      0.08

    Otsu threshold on [0.02, 0.05, 0.10, 0.08, 0.03, 0.12]:
      Bimodal split → threshold = 0.07

    HAC at 0.07:
      Cluster A: {RA, RA of knee}           (distance 0.02 < 0.07)
      Cluster B: {Arthritis, OA}            (distance 0.08 > 0.07 → separate)

    Wait — Arthritis and OA distance is 0.08, above threshold.
    But RA and Arthritis distance is 0.05, below threshold.
    HAC average linkage may group them differently. Let's say:

      Cluster A: {RA, RA of knee, Arthritis} (average dist < 0.07)
      Cluster B: {OA}                         (singleton → kept)

    Within Cluster A, check guards:
      RA vs RA of knee:
        G1 name: both start with "RA" → same
        G2 parent-child: RA → RA of knee edge exists → DIFFERENT → KEEP BOTH
        Guard G2 fires. Both survive.

      RA vs Arthritis:
        G1 name: "Rheumatoid" vs "Arthritis" → different → KEEP BOTH

    Result: all 4 survive in Topic 0. Guards protected them.

  Topic 3 [Drugs]:
    Pairwise:
      MTX ↔ Amlodipine:    0.05
      MTX ↔ Albuterol:     0.08
      Amlodipine ↔ Albuterol: 0.10

    Otsu threshold = 0.06

    Cluster A: {MTX, Amlodipine}  (0.05 < 0.06)
    Cluster B: {Albuterol}

    MTX vs Amlodipine guards:
      G1 name: "Methotrexate" vs "Amlodipine" → DIFFERENT → KEEP BOTH

    All 3 drugs survive. Different drugs, guards protect them.

